Android SQLite Database Tutorial

>SQLite is an open source database
>SQLite support standard relational database features.
>Android comes in with build in SQLite database implementation.
>To create and upgrade a database in your Android application you create a subclass of the
 "SQLiteOpenHelper" class. in the constructor of your subclass you call the super() method of SQLiteOpenHelper


Student.db database name


Cursor--- this interface provides ramdom read-write access to the result set returned by the a database

delete()-- delete the row